<article class="env-example" id="003Z">
  <p><a class="environment-identifier" href="/tag/003Z">Example <span data-tag="003Z">6.2.2</span>.</a> Let $X$ be a finite set with an action of a finite group $G$. Then $|X/ \!  /G|=|X|/|G|$. Note that we are not assuming that the action of $G$ is free. </p>
</article>